Added both GTK2 and GTK3 dev files for building the plugin since some systems (like Ubuntu, where I am writing from) already ship geany with GTK3 and the Makefile didn't work until I installed `libgtk-3-dev`.

Merge pull request #3 from jiafulow/patch-1

Fix error when gd->file_name returns NULL

Fix error when gd->file_name returns NULL

When there is no file in the current session, gd->file_name returns NULL and may cause seg fault. The macro DOC_FILENAME returns a string "untitled" when gd->file_name is NULL, so it is safer.

Geany is released under GPLv2+, the plugin should follow.
